  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Fran\u00e7ois Massion's article, \"Terminology in the Age of AI: The Transformation of Terminology Theory and Practice,\" published in the Journal of Translation Studies, has garnered attention with 5 citations, reflecting its influence in the field. The work is cited by various academic venues, including Lebende Sprachen and Tradum\u00e0tica tecnologies de la traducci\u00f3, indicating its relevance across diverse scholarly discussions.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Fran\u00e7ois Massion's work, \"Terminology in the Age of AI: The Transformation of Terminology Theory and Practice,\" represents a significant contribution to the evolving landscape of translation studies. Published in 2024 in the Journal of Translation Studies, this article has received 5 citations to date, underscoring its academic impact and the reception of its ideas on terminology theory within the modern context of artificial intelligence.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The influence of this research can be observed through its citations in various venues such as Lebende Sprachen and Tradum\u00e0tica tecnologies de la traducci\u00f3, as well as in interdisciplinary discussions reflected in three articles and one book chapter. These citations span multiple countries, including Germany, Austria, and China, showcasing the global reach and diverse perspectives engaged with Massion's insights on AI's impact on terminology.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">While the article has not yet sparked discussion on social platforms like Reddit or Wikipedia, its academic pedigree is reinforced by proven downstream reuse, evidenced by the five instances where its materials have enabled further research. This indication of practical application speaks to the work's relevance and the broader implications of terminology in transitioning fields influenced by technological advancements.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Overall, the trajectory of Massion's work, from its conceptual foundations to its academic citations, reflects the transformative dialogue surrounding terminology theory as it adapts to the challenges and opportunities presented by artificial intelligence. As the scholarly community continues to explore these intersections, this article stands as a critical resource for future inquiries into AI's role in translation and terminology practices.</p>",
